<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Labor and parts quoted separately &mdash; here&rsquo;s why that matters</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Most appliance repair companies in Los Angeles use flat-rate BlueBook pricing &mdash; a single bundled number that covers labor and parts before the technician has diagnosed anything. It sounds convenient. But a drain pump replacement and a control board failure are completely different jobs with very different part costs. Bundling them into a flat rate before diagnosis means someone is paying more than they should.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first, then quote. The $89 diagnostic fee covers the full diagnosis. Once we know what failed, we give you two numbers: labor and the specific OEM part. You see both before approving anything. You know what you&rsquo;re paying for &mdash; and why.</p>
      <p>Washer repairs in LA have one specific pattern worth knowing: stacked washer-dryer units in WeHo, Silver Lake, and Koreatown apartments are among the most common calls we handle. The compact installations, limited access, and high-use patterns of rental units mean these machines see failures earlier than freestanding units in houses. Most are repairable and worth fixing &mdash; a new stacked unit plus installation is a significant expense.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="transparency-block">
      <div class="tr-card them">
        <h3>Flat-Rate BlueBook pricing</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Single price before diagnosis</li>
          <li>Labor and parts bundled &mdash; no breakdown</li>
          <li>Drain pump and control board priced the same</li>
          <li>Price padded for uncertainty on every job</li>
          <li>You don&rsquo;t know what the part costs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="tr-card us">
        <h3>Our approach &mdash; labor + parts separate</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Diagnose first, then quote</li>
          <li>Labor and parts as separate line items</li>
          <li>Simple repairs cost less than complex ones</li>
          <li>You see exactly what the OEM part costs</li>
          <li>$89 diagnostic applied to the total</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block">
      <div class="tip-label">&#9888; Stacked washer-dryer units in LA apartments</div>
      <p>If you have a stacked unit in a WeHo, Silver Lake, or Koreatown apartment &mdash; the labor range may include an access surcharge depending on the installation. We assess access when we arrive and confirm the total before starting. Stacked units are a significant part of our LA washer repair calls and our technicians know these configurations well.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Labor Rates by Repair Type &mdash; Los Angeles 2026</p>
    <h2>What washing machine repair labor costs in Los Angeles</h2>
