<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Cost Factors</p>
    <h2>What affects washing machine repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128295;</div><h3>Front-load vs. top-load</h3><p>Front-load washers have more complex door seals, drum bearings, and spider arms that fail in specific ways. Top-load units have simpler access but different failure points. Labor time differs by configuration.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128218;</div><h3>Stacked unit access</h3><p>Stacked washer-dryer units in LA apartments require working in tight spaces &mdash; sometimes the dryer has to come off to access the washer properly. This adds labor time and is reflected in the quote before we start.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Brand and part cost</h3><p>Samsung, LG, and Whirlpool drain pumps are inexpensive and widely available. Miele and Bosch use proprietary European components at a significant premium &mdash; which is why we quote parts separately so you see the real cost.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128197;</div><h3>Age of the unit</h3><p>Control boards and drum bearings for older models (10+ years) are sometimes discontinued or sourced with lead times. We check parts availability before quoting repair so there are transparent pricing.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127968;</div><h3>Rental vs. owner-occupied</h3><p>High-use rental washers &mdash; common in WeHo, Silver Lake, and Koreatown multi-unit buildings &mdash; see door latch, drain pump, and bearing failures earlier than owner-occupied units. We work with property managers frequently for exactly this reason.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128167;</div><h3>LA hard water impact</h3><p>LA&rsquo;s 300&ndash;400 mg/L TDS hard water builds up in pump screens, inlet valve filters, and drum seals. This can appear as a pump failure when it&rsquo;s actually a clog. Diagnosis first means we don&rsquo;t replace a pump that just needs cleaning.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Repair vs. Replace</p>
    <h2>When to repair a washer, when to replace it</h2>
    <p class="lead">We give you an honest assessment after diagnosis &mdash; the same one we&rsquo;d give if it were our own machine.</p>
    <div class="rvr-grid">
      <div class="rvr-card repair">
        <h3>Repair makes sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Unit is under 10 years old</li>
          <li>Total repair (labor + parts) is under 50% of replacement value</li>
          <li>Stacked unit &mdash; replacement plus installation is expensive</li>
          <li>Miele or Bosch &mdash; these last 15+ years with proper repair</li>
          <li>Single component failure (pump, latch, belt)</li>
          <li>High-end front-loader under 8 years old</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rvr-card replace">
        <h3>Replace makes more sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Budget top-loader is 10&ndash;12+ years old</li>
          <li>Drum bearing failed on a unit under 5 years old (manufacturing defect)</li>
          <li>Multiple components failing simultaneously</li>
          <li>Control board cost exceeds 60% of unit replacement value</li>
          <li>Parts are discontinued with no ETA</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

